China calls 3 slain by police 'terrorists'

 
 By AUSTIN RAMZY The New York Times
 


 
 
 This article was published July 15, 2015 at 3:41 a.m.
 
 
 
 

Police in the northeastern Chinese city of Shenyang said Tuesday that they had shot and killed three men who belonged to a terrorist organization and that the three lashed out with knives and shouted jihadist slogans when officers tried to enter their apartment.
